OL,6,F"We're really pleased and privileged
OL,7,Fto have people like Helen and some of
OL,8,Fher peers who are willing to give up
OL,9,Ftheir time and energy to come and help
OL,10,Fus improve and give us that value of
OL,11,Flived experience on our improvement
OL,12,Fjourney."
OL,14,FDespite a difficult few years after
OL,15,Fleaving Ty Llidiard, Helen is now on a
OL,16,Fbetter path too, having recently
OL,17,Ffinished her first year's training to
OL,18,Fbecome a doctor, as she hopes to make
OL,19,Fa difference to those in need in more
OL,20,Fways than one.
